## Fix: Base URI persistence across server restarts and domain switches

**Context:** Domains with a custom Base URI were seeing it revert to
`https://databricks-ontology.com` after a server restart or domain reload.
This was caused by three compounding gaps: (1) `read_version` never read the
canonical `domains.base_uri` column from the DB, relying solely on the
`ontology` JSONB blob; (2) `write_version` could blank the column when the
ontology JSON held an empty string; (3) empty-string `base_uri` values in
session were not treated as missing, so `DEFAULT_BASE_URI` fallback was not
triggered consistently.

**Changes:**

1. `src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/store.py` ‚Äî `read_version`:
   also SELECT `d.base_uri` and merge it into `ontology.base_uri` when the
   ontology JSON has no value.
2. `src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/store.py` ‚Äî `write_version`:
   use a `CASE WHEN` in the `ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE` so an empty incoming
   `base_uri` never overwrites an existing value in the `domains` column.
3. `src/back/objects/session/DomainSession.py` ‚Äî `export_for_save`: add
   `base_uri_auto` to the exported ontology blob so the auto/manual flag
   survives a registry round-trip.
4. `src/back/objects/session/DomainSession.py` ‚Äî `ensure_generated_content`:
   change `get("base_uri", DEFAULT_BASE_URI)` to `get("base_uri") or
   DEFAULT_BASE_URI` so an empty string also triggers the fallback.
5. `src/back/objects/ontology/Ontology.py` ‚Äî `generate_owl`: same empty-
   string guard.
6. `src/back/objects/mapping/Mapping.py` ‚Äî `generate_r2rml`: same guard.
7. `src/api/routers/domains.py` ‚Äî four call-sites: same guard.

**Modified files:**
- `src/back/objects/registry/store/lakebase/store.py`
- `src/back/objects/session/DomainSession.py`
- `src/back/objects/ontology/Ontology.py`
- `src/back/objects/mapping/Mapping.py`
- `src/api/routers/domains.py`

**Test result:** 2450 passed, 15 skipped.
